== Description ==

The '''BIM Nudge''' tools are a set of tools that incrementally move, rotate, or change the height of selected objects. For the rotation a fixed value of 45° is used. The other operations use a nudge distance.

The nudge distance can be set to a fixed value or to ''Auto'' mode, which automatically scales the nudge distance based on the current view zoom level.

== Usage ==

# Select one or more objects.
# Use any of the keyboard shortcuts listed below.

== Nudge tools ==

''Listed are the version 1.2 shortcuts.''

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Tool !! Shortcut !! Description
|-
| [[BIM_Nudge_Switch|Nudge Switch]] || {{KEY|Alt}} {{KEY|/}} || Switches the nudge mode between auto and fixed distance
|-
| [[BIM_Nudge_Up|Nudge Up]] || {{KEY|Alt}} {{KEY|Up}} || Moves the selection up on the working plane
|-
| [[BIM_Nudge_Down|Nudge Down]] || {{KEY|Alt}} {{KEY|Down}} || Moves the selection down on the working plane
|-
| [[BIM_Nudge_Left|Nudge Left]] || {{KEY|Alt}} {{KEY|Left}} || Moves the selection left on the working plane
|-
| [[BIM_Nudge_Right|Nudge Right]] || {{KEY|Alt}} {{KEY|Right}} || Moves the selection right on the working plane
|-
| [[BIM_Nudge_RotateLeft|Nudge Rotate Left]] || {{KEY|Alt}} {{KEY|,}} || Rotates the selection counterclockwise
|-
| [[BIM_Nudge_RotateRight|Nudge Rotate Right]] || {{KEY|Alt}} {{KEY|.}} || Rotates the selection clockwise
|-
| [[BIM_Nudge_Extend|Nudge Extend]] || {{KEY|Alt}} {{KEY|PgUp}} || Increases the height of objects in the selection
|-
| [[BIM_Nudge_Shrink|Nudge Shrink]] || {{KEY|Alt}} {{KEY|PgDown}} || Decreases the height of objects in the selection
|}

== Nudge distance ==

The nudge distance is displayed in the BIM [[Status_Bar|Status Bar]] at the bottom of the FreeCAD window. You can:

* Click the nudge value to change it manually.
* Enter a custom value in the current unit system.
* Set it to ''Auto'' to automatically scale based on the zoom level.

== Notes ==

* The center of rotation for the rotate tools is the center of the overall bounding box of the selected objects. The rotation axis is parallel to the Z-axis of the working plane.
* The extend and shrink tools only change objects that have a {{PropertyData|Height}} property.


